article.headline: ETSU 65, SIU-Edwardsville 62
article.story: CHARLESTON, W.Va. -- Kevin Tiggs scored 19 points, including a dunk with 24 seconds to play to help East Tennessee State beat Southern Illinois-Edwardsville 65-62 Saturday in the second round of the Charleston Classic. Tiggs made one of two free throws with 41 seconds to play to put ETSU ahead 62-60. On the Cougars' next possession, ETSU's Mike Smith stole the ball and drove to the basket. Smith missed the layup, but Tiggs was there to grab the rebound and dunk it. After an Edwardsville miss, Smith was fouled and made one of two free throws to put the Buccaneers ahead 65-62 with 9.1 seconds to play. The Cougars' Aaron Garriott missed a potential game-tying 3-pointer from the top of the key at the buzzer. Mark Yelovich led the Cougars with 15 points.
